# MCP SERVER USAGE RULES

## filesystem
Use to read project files directly — never ask user to paste code.
Priority read order for build tasks:
  1. package.json (check installed packages first)
  2. supabase/migrations/ (check DB schema before querying)
  3. lib/engines/[relevant engine] (check logic before modifying)
  4. req_0X_*.md (only the relevant domain doc)
Max 5 files per session via filesystem.

## git
Use before any bug fix:
  - git log --oneline -10 (find when bug was introduced)
  - git diff HEAD~1 (see what changed in last commit)
  - git blame [file] (find who changed which line)
Never guess what changed — always use git to verify.

## sequential-thinking
ALWAYS activate for tasks that:
  - Span more than 2 files
  - Involve calculation engine changes
  - Require understanding DB schema + API + UI together
This server prevents context overflow by forcing step-by-step
reasoning instead of one massive think block.

## crawl4ai
Use for data refresh tasks only:
  - UMR/UMP regional minimum wages (wajar-gaji)
  - NJOP land price indices (wajar-tanah)
  - BPS salary survey data
  - Cost of living indices (wajar-hidup)
Always save scraped data to lib/data/[source]-[year].json
Never scrape in real-time during user calculator sessions.

## browser-use
Use for:
  - Automated UI testing of calculator flows
  - Scraping sites that require JavaScript rendering
  - Testing premium gate behavior (free vs paid)
Set headless: true for all automation.
Never use browser-use for simple HTTP scraping — use crawl4ai.

## gitnexus
Use for semantic code search across repo history.
Only keep if it provides semantic search beyond plain git commands.
If redundant with git server, prefer git.

## hermes (DEFERRED — Legion Bot Phase 2)
Only activate for Legion Bot multi-agent tasks.
Set MAX_DELEGATION_DEPTH=2 to prevent recursive loops.
Never use hermes for single-product tasks.

## CONTEXT BUDGET WITH MCP
Each MCP tool call costs ~500–2000 tokens.
Max MCP calls per session: 10
If you need more than 10 MCP calls: decompose into subagents.

## REMOVED SERVERS
- ruflo: REMOVED — causes context overflow (215+ tools)
- symphony: REMOVED — wrong stack (PHP/Symfony, project is Next.js/TS)
